    <stitle>VT 365 Diesel Engine - 2004 Model Year - FRONT COVER, VIBRATION DAMPER, and GEROTOR OIL PUMP - Removal -
        Front Oil Seal and Wear Sleeve
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26505.2.3" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="4">
        <title>Front Oil Seal and Wear Sleeve</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The VT 365 is not equipped with a wear sleeve during factory production. Wear sleeves are
                    available with an oil seal service kit.
                </para>
            </note>
            <note>
                <para>If removing only the seal, do steps 1 through 3. Otherwise, remove seal and wear sleeve doing
                    steps 1 through 4.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To prevent personal injury or death, wear safety glasses with side shields to protect eyes.</para>
            </warning>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, do not immerse damper in petroleum based solvents. Damage to rubber
                    damping element may result.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f2650504" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd06/D0640.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Holes for slide hammer</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With an awl and hammer, punch two holes 180&#176; apart in the front oil seal.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650505" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd06/D0641A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Slide hammer</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Thread a slide hammer with correct size screw in one of the two holes.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide hammer until one side of the seal begins to pull out the gerotor cover. Move the slide
                hammer to the other hole and repeat until the front oil seal is removed completely.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The following steps are necessary, if the engine has a front wear sleeve. Wear sleeves are only
                    available in oil seal service kits.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Do the following steps to install the front wear sleeve remover :</para>
            <figure id="f2650506" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd06/D0642A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Removal of front wear sleeve</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f2650507" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd06/D0643.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Front wear sleeve removed</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Front wear sleeve</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Install the tools two half shell ridges behind the front wear sleeve.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Place the threaded shaft and pulling flange inside the two shells while holding the
                    shells together.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Thread the shaft up to the crankshaft, and apply tension to the two half shells. Remove
                    wear sleeve.
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
